{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 7 reveals that other frequently occurring author keywords include \"human, \" \"artificial intelligence, \" \"female, \" \"breast neoplasms, \" \"article, \" \"breast tumour, \" \"machine learning, \" \"diagnostic imaging, \" \"deep learning, \" and \"sensitivity, \" all ranking highly after \"mammography. \"",
    "Using a clustering algorithm on the keyword network allows for the identification of various themes within a given field.",
    "Each cluster or theme can be depicted on a specific type of graph known as a strategic or thematic map [18].",
    "In this map, each bubble signifies a network cluster.",
    "The name of the bubble corresponds to the word with the highest frequency within the cluster."
  ]
}